title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:D]]></fr:tex> be two elements of a dcpo <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>. We say that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em>apart</fr:em> from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex>, written <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\mathrel {\#} y]]></fr:tex>, if there exists a Scott-open subset <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U\subseteq  D]]></fr:tex> that contains one but not both of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>(Adapted from <fr:link
type="local"
href="dejong-2021.xml"
addr="dejong-2021"
title="Sharp elements and apartness in domains">de Jong</fr:link>.)</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>